At this point we’re at 150mph. Up ahead there is a massive inferno and you can only look in terror as it’s the only thing that you see. Y’all does anyone else feel like this is legit the worst time of the year? The millisecond that thanksgiving break ends it’s a nonstop nightmare until Christmas break. Without fail there seems to be one thousand things to do. It’s like earlier in the semester, I was going like 40mph, but now I’m at 100mph and the cosmic car is swerving and I’m almost hitting things and I have my whole family in the car and they are screaming and so am I. Being a doctor sometimes is difficult but this is even worse... And there is also a blizzard going on and I can’t see and the radio is really loud and all the window and doors have flown off the car and we’re sitting and shivering. Then you are covered in it and you are just praying to any deity above to spare you.
